lish, German, Italian, and Swedish globe makers. The 120 colour illustrations allow the reader to savour these rare and unusual works and include numerous detailed reproductions of both terrestrial and celestial map images. Sphæræ Mundi charts developments and changes over three centuries of globe making, considering the globes as indicators of scientific advance and geographical exploration as well as artifacts and providing a unique opportunity to become familiar with these complex and beautiful objects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCartographyxHistory. 0aCelestial globesxHistory. 0aGlobes célestesxCataloguesxQuébecxMontréalxMontrealxKatalogxMuseum. 0aGlobes terrestresxCatalogues. 0aGlobesxCatalogsxQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aGlobesxHistory. 0aGlobeszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvCatalogs. 7aTravel / Special Interest / General.2bisacsh1 aDerome, Robert*, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGauvin, Jean-Francois, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKrogt, Peter Van Der*, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356907240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773569072423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773569072/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles